      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:97:16",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّمَا جُعِلَتِ التَّقِيَّةُ لِيُحْقَنَ بِهَا الدَّمُ فَإِذَا بَلَغَ الدَّمَ فَلَيْسَ تَقِيَّةٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Safwan, from Shuayb Al Haddad, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘But rather, the dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>) has been Made to be for saving the blood by it. So when it comes to the blood (to be spilt anyway), then there would be no dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "16. Abu Ali al-Ash’ari has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from Safwan from Shu’ayb al-Haddad from Muhammad ibn Muslim from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “ Al-Taqiyyah is made law to save lives. Once it (danger) is already there to take lives, then there is no al-Taqiyyah .” "
        ]
      }
    },
